               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>The day that this misfortune happened, 
               <persName id="t17681019-43-person434">
                  Tim 
                  Simpson 
               <interp inst="t17681019-43-person434" type="surname" value="Simpson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17681019-43-person434" type="given" value="Tim"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17681019-43-person434" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and I went into Bartholomew-fair, and then I went up to Islington, in order to go to a friend's house that I expected was gone to Waltham-cross; I returned by the King of Prussia, and met Simpson again; we came by the river side, and stopped at the London Spaw to make water; he went forward, and when I came up I found 
               <persName id="t17681019-43-person435">
                  Tim 
                  Simpson 
               <interp inst="t17681019-43-person435" type="surname" value="Simpson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17681019-43-person435" type="given" value="Tim"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17681019-43-person435" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and the man on the ground; I took hold of the man's arm, and said, what is the matter; he struck me with a stick, and knocked me down, I got up, and he knocked me down again; I put my hand upon the rail, and jumped over he followed me, and said, you dog, I will have your life; he got hold of my coat, and pulled it off, then I made off, and went to my lodging.</p>
